LINUX COMMANDS

  1. cd - to change directory.
  2. cd / - to goto the root folder
  3. pwd - to print the current working directory.
  4. ls -l - to list files in a directory with their details.
  5. ls - to list files in a directory.
  6. man - to know details about any linux command.
  7. mkdir - to create a directory.
  8. touch - to create a .txt file.
  9. cp - to copy a file.
  10. cp -r - to copy a directory.
  11. mv - to move or rename a file.
  12. rm - to remove a file.
  13. Top - to print all processes details.
  14. ps - process status.
  15. ps -a - tell about active processes.
  16. grep - it searches the given input.
  17. ping - to know connectivity of an ip address or a website.
  18. ip addr - to find the ip address
  19. wget - to download from the provided link.
  20. sudo - run a command as a superuser.
